         <abstract>
            <p>Futures markets are hard to manipulate or monopolize because of actual and potential competition from the cash commodity. Either manipulation or monopoly depends on secrecy. The futures exchanges have the appropriate incentive to establish the optimal degree of secrecy, which promotes trading even as it facilitates manipulation. The loss from monopoly and manipulation cannot exceed the gains from trading any contract, so it is never right to limit entry.</p>
         </abstract>
